ary lens\nlocated in the Galactic bulge with a distance $6.7\\pm 0.3$ kpc from the Earth.\nThe individual lens components with masses $0.9\\pm 0.3\\ M_\\odot$ and $0.5\\pm\n0.1\\ M_\\odot$ are separated with a semi-major axis of $a=2.5 \\pm 1.0$ AU and\norbiting each other with a period $P=3.1 \\pm 1.3$ yr. The event demonstrates\nthat it is possible to extract detailed information about binary lens systems\nfrom well-resolved lensing light curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Apr 2011 09:16:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
